      "title": "Two-Phase Stitch Enrichment Strategy",
      "description": "As part of the UI/UX Pro Max Specialist integration, we have discovered a gap between the static HTM...",
      "content": "# Story UIUX-4.6: Two-Phase Stitch Enrichment Strategy\n\n## 1. Context & Objective\nAs part of the UI/UX Pro Max Specialist integration, we have discovered a gap between the static HTML/CSS generated by Stitch and the dynamic, highly interactive capabilities defined in our comprehensive Pro Max library. To solve this, we are implementing a **Two-Phase Stitch Enrichment Strategy**. \n\nThe objective is to decouple the initial visual layout generation (Phase 1) from the enrichment of micro-interactions and logic (Phase 2), utilizing a Prompt Injection pattern. This allows the UI Spec to serve as a single source of truth for both static and dynamic requirements.\n\n## 2. Acceptance Criteria (AC)\n- **AC1 (Template Update):** The UI Spec template (`template.md`) must be updated to include two new sections: `[STITCH_PROMPT_INJECTION]` and `[POST_STITCH_ENRICHMENT_LOGIC]`.\n- **AC2 (Workflow Patching):** The `workflow-entry.md` and `iwish-bmm-code-review.md` must enforce the inclusion of these sections and validate their implementation during code review.\n- **AC3 (Enrichment Workflow):** A new workflow, `iwish-bmm-enrich-ux.md`, must be created to handle the Phase 2 enrichment logic.\n- **AC4 (Skill Updates):** The `ui-ux` Skill must be updated to output the required `[STITCH_PROMPT_INJECTION]` block based on its interaction library.\n- **AC5 (Validation):** The implementation must be successfully tested on a sample (e.g., the Distro Landing Page) to confirm both phases execute flawlessly.\n- **AC6 (Auto-Trigger Touchpoints):** Master Design defaults to mandatory enrichment. UI Spec generation uses a 3-level scoring system to determine if enrichment is required (Enrich-UX Score).\n- **AC7 (Dev Readiness Gate):** Vegeta Dev workflow (`iwish-bmm-dev-story.md`) halts if UI Spec has `Enrichment_Required: true` but `[POST_STITCH_ENRICHMENT_LOGIC]` is empty, unless user types `APPROVE_OVERRIDE`.\n- **AC8 (Orchestrator Role):** The `ui-ux` agent acts as the Domain-Specific Orchestrator for Frontend/Design, managing the UI Spec -> Stitch -> Enrich-UX execution pipeline to reduce user cognitive load.\n- **AC9 (Visual Fidelity Gate):** Refactor `stitch-design-taste` to `visual-fidelity-gate` and broaden the \"Absolute Source of Truth\" to be the \"Approved Master Design Source\" (e.g. Figma, Stitch, Custom UI Kit) rather than hardcoding Stitch.\n\n## 3. Implementation Tasks\n- **Task 1:** Modify `.agent/workflows/template.md` to append the new sections.\n- **Task 2:** Update `.agent/workflows/workflow-entry.md` to explicitly require the `[STITCH_PROMPT_INJECTION]` and replace `stitch-design-taste` references with `visual-fidelity-gate`.\n- **Task 3:** Create `.agent/workflows/iwish-bmm-enrich-ux.md` for the specialist enrichment process.\n- **Task 4:** Modify `.agent/workflows/iwish-bmm-code-review.md` to include validation for the `[POST_STITCH_ENRICHMENT_LOGIC]` section.\n- **Task 5:** Update `.agent/skills/ui-ux/SKILL.md` to output the correct prompt injection payload and adopt the Orchestrator behavior.\n- **Task 6:** Update `.agent/workflows/iwish-bmm-create-ui-spec.md` to add Enrich-UX Scoring logic and trigger rule.\n- **Task 7:** Update `.agent/workflows/iwish-bmm-dev-story.md` (Vegeta) to add the Readiness Halt (Gate Option A).\n- **Task 8:** Ensure `iwish-bmm-enrich-ux.md` handles the auto-trigger gracefully.\n- **Task 9:** Rename and update `.agent/skills/visual-fidelity-gate/SKILL.md` to support dynamic Master Design Sources.\n\n## 4. Traceability Matrix\n| AC | Mapped Tasks | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| AC1 | Task 1 | ✅ DONE |\n| AC2 | Task 2, Task 4 | ✅ DONE |\n| AC3 | Task 3 | ✅ DONE |\n| AC4 | Task 5 | ✅ DONE |\n| AC5 | (Verification) | ✅ DONE |\n| AC6 | Task 6 | ✅ DONE |\n| AC7 | Task 7 | ✅ DONE |\n\n## 5. Dev Notes (Project Memory)\n- **Tracer Bullet:** The vertical slice for this story involves generating a UI spec with the prompt injection, passing it through Stitch, and then enriching the approved UI spec with dynamic JavaScript/CSS logic, which is then strictly verified by the code review agent.\n- Ensure the prompt injection block focuses only on instructions Stitch can parse effectively without breaking the static layout generation.\n\n## 6. Enrich-UX Scoring Criteria\nTo determine if a UI Spec requires enrichment, the `ui-ux` agent will calculate the following score (0-10):\n\n| Factor | Description (Score 0-5) | Weight |\n|---|---|---|\n| **E1: Interaction Complexity** | 0=Static CRUD, 2=Hovers/State transitions, 4=Drag-drop/Data viz, 5=High-interaction SaaS Landing (GSAP/Scrolljacking) | x2 |\n| **E2: Emotional Impact (WOW Factor)** | 0=Admin settings, 2=Efficiency Dashboard, 4=Webstore checkout, 5=Acquisition/Conversion funnels | x2 |\n| **E3: Feedback Density** | 0=Standard buttons, 3=Complex counters/Progress, 5=Continuous AI feedback loops (Pulse/Glow) | x1 |\n| **E4: Brand Kinetic Identity** | 0=Standard Tailwind/AntD, 2=Custom token tweaks, 5=Core brand kinetic signatures (e.g. Distro Neon Mint glow) | x1 |\n\n**Formula:** `Score = (E1*2 + E2*2 + E3 + E4) / 30 * 10`\n\n**Decision Matrix:**\n- **0-3: SKIP ENRICHMENT** (Static HTML/CSS is sufficient).\n- **4-6: STANDARD ENRICHMENT** (Inject CSS transitions, hover states, fade-ins).\n- **7-10: PRO-MAX ENRICHMENT** (Inject JS Observers, GSAP/Framer, complex state choreography).\n\n---\n### 🛡️ QA Simulator Guardian Scorecard (Pre-Execution Audit)\n\n| Axis | Score (1-10) | Justification / Finding |\n|---|---|---|\n| Functional Correctness | 9 | Clear separation of static layout and dynamic enrichment resolves the capability gap. |\n| Data Integrity & State | 9 | Using UI Spec as the source of truth maintains document and state integrity. |\n| Security & Validation | 9 | Code review patches ensure the enriched logic is validated strictly. |\n| Performance & Scalability | 9 | Two phases decouple latency constraints during the initial visual generation. |\n| Error Handling & Recovery | 8 | Enrichment phase provides a clear fallback if Stitch fails to interpret the prompt. |\n| Code Quality & Maintainability | 10 | Follows I-Wish design patterns by modifying existing structured workflows. |\n| UX Empathy | 10 | Results in a richer, more engaging end-user experience (Pro Max level). |\n| **TOTAL AVERAGE** | **9.1 / 10** | **PASS** |\n\n---",
