      "content": "# Story 1.16: Solution Source Research Before Create or Enhance\n\n## Objective\n\nAdd a canonical workflow for researching existing internal capabilities, external repos, and open modules before deciding to create a new skill or enhance an existing one.\n\n## Why\n\nThe system already had `create-skill`, `enhance-skill`, `register-skill-pack`, and `absorb-repo`, but it lacked a clear pre-decision research lane for requests like:\n\n- find a repo that solves this\n- is there already a skill for this\n- compare internal capability vs external module\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- a canonical supportive workflow exists for solution-source research\n- Orch can route natural-language requests for repo/skill/framework discovery into that workflow\n- `create-skill` and `enhance-skill` explicitly reference this pre-decision research step\n- the inventory and command catalog recognize this workflow as part of the canonical surface",
